review_blob: Coffee, chocolate, roasted malts, brown sugar in aroma. Pours black with huge tan head. Taste is medium sweet with coffee, vanilla, mead, liqueur, chocolate and molasses. Finish is medium bitter, alcohol warms a throat. Overall very good, uncompromising Impy.

Ice tea in aroma followed by citrus and tropical fruits. Pours amber with white head. Taste as well as nose reminds the ice tea with medium to high bitterness at the finish, bit astringent. Overall it lacks of drinkability for such a light beer.

Vanilla, liquorice, caramel, coffee and chocolate in aroma. Pours dark brown with beige head. Taste is surprisingly dry with coffee and dark chocolate. Vanilla, liquorice and caramel are in the background. Finish is medium bitter. Alcohol is noticeable but not disturbing. Overall not bad but too dry for a Baltic Porter.

Aroma of grains, carrot, multivitamin and grass. Pours golden with white head. Taste is medium dry with grain, some fruits, mead and spices. Finish is medium bitter. Overall unusual, solid session beer.

Peach, apricot and banana in aroma. Pours orange with white head. Taste is medium sweet, fruity with peach, apricot, spices. Low bitterness at the finish. Overall this is absolutely not a barley wine. It is more like Belgian Strong, however it is tasty, easy to drink beer.

Maybe aroma is not the most complex but hops are doing here great job - citrus all the way. Pours golden, clear with white head. Taste is dry, again very hoppy with citrus notes at the foreground. Finish is medium bitter, a little bit boozy, not disturbing. Overall very good IPA.

Caramel, vanilla, some dark fruits in aroma. Pours mahogany with nice and stable beige creamy head. Taste is medium sweet with caramel, fruits and vanilla. Powerful bitterness at the finish makes this one bit unbalanced but ok, it would not be the Arrogant Bastard without it. Overall solid but the barrel notes could be more exposed.

Melon, pear, apricot, peach and citrus in aroma. Pours golden, clear with white head. Taste is medium dry with citrus, pear, melon and some booze. Medium to low bitterness at the finish. Overall good, very drinkable.

Spices, citrus, some hay in aroma. Pours golden, clear with white head. Taste is dry with spices, citrus, some bergamot. Finish is moderate bitter, alcohol is hidden very well. Overall interesting, dangerously drinkable brew.

Tropical fruits in aroma, multivitamin, citrus. Pours golden, very hazy with white head. Taste is complex, malty sweetness at the beginning, after that medium citrus sourness is coming followed by moderate hoppy finish. Overall very drinkable, refreshing stuff.

Coffee, chocolate, forest fruits in aroma. Pours dark brown with tan head. Taste is medium dry. There is coffee, ash, chocolate, forest fruits. Finish is medium bitter, body is medium to full. Overall good.
Cocoa, ash, herbs and coffee in aroma. Pours dark brown with beige head. Taste is medium dry with cocoa, bit ashiness and coffee. Finish is medium bitter. Overall very good, drinkable porter.

Peat, raisins, plums, caramel in aroma. Pours dar brown with perfect beige head. Taste is medium sweet with dark fruits, some caramel, peat and bread. Finish is medium bitter, body is full, alcohol is hidden extremely well. Overall this one matched my high expectations. Great beer.

Coffee, some fruits and chocolate in aroma. Pours dark brown with beige head. Taste is medium dry, coffee predominates, some chocolate is also noticeable. Finish is low bitter. Overall good, easy to drink beer.

Milk chocolate, some coffee in aroma. Pours dark brown with weak beige head, overcarbonated. Taste is medium sweet with milk chocolate and caffe latte. Low to medium bitter finish. Overall disappointing aroma, slightly better taste but lack of smoothness makes this one average at best.

Chocolate, coffee and citrus in aroma. Pours dark brown with nice tan head. Taste is medium dry with dark chocolate, ash, coffee. Medium grapefruit-like bitterness at the finish. Slightly overcarbonated but still very good.

Spices, citrus and grain in aroma. Pours golden with white head. Taste is dry with spices and citrus, finish is low bitter. Very drinkable but not watery, medium carbonated brew. Overall very good for spring/summer time.
Chocolate and coffee in aroma. Poursalmost pitch black with beige head. Taste is medium sweet with cocoa and some coffee. Finish is medium bitter, salty. Body is medium to full. Overall very good.

Citrus, pine, roasted sunflower seeds in aroma. Pours dark brown with white head. Taste is medium dry, hoppy with citrus and pine. There is also some booze and coffee. Finish is medium bitter both hoppy and boozy. Overall solid but the presence of alcohol is too sharp.

Aroma of chocolate, coffee, cherries, forest fruits, wood, booze and vanilla. Pours pitch black with tan head. Taste is medium dry, tart with blackberries, black currant, chocolate, coffee, red wine. Body is medium to full. It is more like blend of Imperial Stout and red wine. Low to medium bitter finish. Alcohol is very well hidden. Overall very complex, unusual beer which is definitely worth a try. Love it.
Aroma of toffee, caramel and Werthers Original candies. Pours amber with white head. Taste is medium sweet with caramel and toffee, low bitter finish. Overall quite drinkable and solid brew.

Aroma of chocolate, coffee, some vanilla and roasted malts. Pours pitch black with tan head which quikly disappears. Taste is medium dry, quite flat with chocolate and coffee, finish is spicy but not exaggerated. Overall it deffinitely lacks more body and complexity in taste. Not bad but I am expecting more from Impies.
Lemon, incense in aroma. Pours golden with white head. Taste is medium dry with predomination of lemon. Low bitterness at the finish. Overall pretty one-dimensional brew.

Not intense aroma of chocolate, coffee, vanilla, dark fruits and booze. Pours dark brown with tan head. Taste is rather dry with dark fruits, chocolate and booze. It lacks body, too watery for an Impy. Overall disappointing taking into account its potential.

Aroma of chocolate, coffee with burned electronics at the background. Pours black with tan head. Taste follows the nose, full body, creamy mouthfeel makes this one very smooth. Finish is medium bitter. Overall very good, I hope that Imperial Stoutopia will be released soon.

Coffee, some chocoale in aroma. Pours dark brown with beige head. Taste is moderate sour, cheap coffee-like. Unfortunately this one is way overcarbonated which decreases drinkability. Low bitterness at the finish. Overall average at best.

Aroma of lemon, barnyard, horse blanket. Pours golden with tall white head. Taste is medium sour, tart with lemon, funky and vinegar. No bitterness at all. Overall very refreshing and quite easy to drink lambic.
Grain, citrus, some booze in aroma. Pours golden with rather weak white head. Taste is quite boozy, bit grainy with some citrus. Bitterness comes mainly from alcohol. Overall disappointing.

Nice aroma of citrus, ripe pineapple, apricot. Pours golden with white head. Taste is dry, very hoppy with citrus and tropical fruits. Moderate bitter finish. Overall extremely good, very drinkable brew.

Aroma of caramel, some bread and wet cardboard. Pours brown with beige head. Taste is medium sweet with caramel, bread, some melanoidins, low bitterness at the finish. Alcohol well hidden. Overall pretty simple beer, you will not find nothing spectacular here but its quite tasty and drinkable.
beer_name: Pinta Ce nest pas IPA Bruin

review_blob: Aroma of barnyard, leather, horse blanket and forest fruits. Pours copper with white head. Taste is very refreshing, bit tart, fruity with blackberries and other forest fruits, lemon and orange. No bitterness. Overall well done.
beer_name: Jan Olbracht Rzemielniczy Piotrek z Bagien Funky Wild Fruit Jeyna

review_blob: Chocolate, caramel, some coffee in aroma. Pours dark brown with tan head. Taste is medium sweet with milk chocolate and slightly sour coffee. Creamy mouthfeel, medium body and low bitterness at the finish. Overall very nice porter. Good job.

Very hoppy aroma with citrus and some pine. Pours dark brown with nice white foamy head. Taste is again, very hoppy, medium sweet malty notes are countered by citrus and pine flavors. Alcohol perfectly covered, bitterness is medium as well as body. Overall perfectly balanced, dangerously drinkable beer. Great stuff.

Funky aroma, leather, barnyard, some ripe gooseberry in the background. Pours orange with white head. Taste is balanced between sour, funky and lemon flavors and sweet, fruity, mainly gooseberry accents. Bitterness does not exist. Overall good, very drinkable, refreshing stuff.
beer_name: Jan Olbracht Rzemielniczy Piotrek z Bagien Funky Wild Fruit Agrest

review_blob: Aroma of apricot, citrus, mango, passionfruit. Pours dark golden with white head. Taste medium dry, very hoppy-first, apricot from the nose disappeared, mostly citrus notes are noticeable. Finish is medium to high bitter. Overall very good.

Coffee, caffe latte, cream in aroma. Pours golden with white head. Taste is medium sweet to sweet with flavor of coffee, cream and sugar at the foreground. Bitterness is low, creamy mouthfeel. Overall interesting, drinkable.

Cardamon, cinnamon, pepper and caramel in aroma. Pours red amber with white head. Taste is very spicy, medium sweet with cinnamon and cardamon, some caramel as well as bread are also there. Alcohol is not noticeable at all. Overall good, easy to drink.

Grapes, gooseberry, muscat in aroma. Pours golden with white head. Taste is medium sweet, with gooseberry, lychee, white wine, bit of alcohol. Finish is medium bitter. Overall outstanding, very drinkable brew that show all strenghts of Nelson Sauvin.

Peach, apricot, banana, some bubblegum in aroma. Pours golden with white head. Taste is medium sweet with peach, spices and maltiness. Alcohol well covered, only noticeable at the finish. Very drinkable considering high ABV%. Overall average Tripel but it means this is very fine beer!

Rather weak aroma of citrus and tropical fruits. Pours golden with white head. Taste is also somewhat disappointing with alcohol not really well covered, some citrus, mango, grain. Finish is medium to low bitter. Overall it is drinkable but you can find many better IPAs on the market.

Smoke, citrus, pine, coffee and chocolate in aroma. Pours almost pitch black with tan head. Taste is medium dry with all components of aroma noticable in flavor. Medium bitterness at the finish. Overall nice smoked stout, I got everything that was promised on the label.

03.07.2016. Vanilla, wood, chocolate, coffee, booze in aroma. Pours pitch black with small tan head. Medium body. Flavor reminds the chocolate vanilla cake soaked with bourbon. Some coffee as well as citrus are also noticeable. Finish is medium bitter. Overall very good.

Nice citrus aroma as well as tropical fruits. Pours orange, hazy with white head. Taste is medium dry with grain, citrus, mango, peach and passionfruit. Finish is medium bitter and boozy. Overall good with potential to be great but the alcoholic finish disturbs bit too much.

Chocolate, caramel, smokiness in aroma. Pours dark brown with beige head. Taste is medium sweet, well balanced between basic beer and smoky notes. There is some chocolate, nuts, coffee as well as peaty and sausage from the fire notes. Bitterness is low. Overall very good.

Cherries, raspberries, cranberries, some vanilla in aroma. Pours red with pink head. Taste is slightly sour, very fruity, some acidic, bit sweet. No bitterness. Overall taste is not as good as nose, too one-dimensional and bit boring.

Coffee, grapes, chocolate, booze, dark fruits and citrus in aroma. Pours pitch black with small but surprisingly stable tan head. Taste is dry with coffee, cognac, chocolate, some wood and fruits. Bitterness is medium to high - grapefruit-like, medium body. Overall very good.

Chocolate and vanilla in aroma. Pours almost black with tan head. Taste is medium dry with chocolate, coffee and vanilla. Bitterness is low to medium. Overall solid porter, nothing extraordinary but drunk with pleasure.

Coffee, booze and some chocolate in aroma. Pours pitch black with brown head. Taste is medium dry, it is like coffee liqueur, alcohol well integrated into the beer, not really covered but not disturbing. Medium bitterness at the finish, both: hoppy and boozy. Overall definitely worth a try as the one of the heaviest Impies on the market.
beer_name: Ngne  / Mikkeller / Brewdog Horizon Tokyo Black

review_blob: Coffee, milk chocolate and smoke in aroma. Pours pitch black with beige head. Taste is similar to nose, quite sour, medium to low sweetness. Medium to full body, finish is medium bitter, slightly boozy. Overall solid sipper, not very complex with excessive sourness from roasted malts.

Hoppy aroma with citrus and tropical fruits. Pours golden with white head. Taste is also very hoppy on the citrus side. Finish is medium to high bitter. Overall good, it could easly be mistaken with regular IPA.
